### EPUB Structure Extractor API
### Requires the REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/v1
@epubPath = /workspace/extractor/my_book.epub
@marpOutput = /workspace/extractor/output/book_presentation.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Health
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Root

GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Health check

GET {{baseUrl}}/health


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# EPUB Processing
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Check LLM connectivity (Ollama)

GET {{apiUrl}}/epub/llm/status

### 2. Extract EPUB structure → DB

# @name extractEpub
POST {{apiUrl}}/epub/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "epub_path": "{{epubPath}}",
  "book_name": "My Book",
  "language": "en",
  "author": "Author Name",
  "images_output_dir": "/workspace/extractor/output/images"
}

### 3. List chapters of an extracted book

GET {{apiUrl}}/epub/chapters?book_id={{extractEpub.response.body.$.book_id}}

### 4. Exclude chapters from AI summarisation (set include=false)

POST {{apiUrl}}/epub/chapters/include
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": "{{extractEpub.response.body.$.book_id}}",
  "chapter_numbers": ["1", "2.1", "3", "4", "5", "6", "21", "22"],
  "include": false
}

### 5. Re-include chapters

POST {{apiUrl}}/epub/chapters/include
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": "{{extractEpub.response.body.$.book_id}}",
  "chapter_numbers": ["1", "2.1"],
  "include": true
}

### 6. Generate AI summaries — all included chapters (requires Ollama, run step 2 first)

POST {{apiUrl}}/epub/summarize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": "{{extractEpub.response.body.$.book_id}}"
}

### 7. Generate AI summaries — specific chapters only

POST {{apiUrl}}/epub/summarize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": "{{extractEpub.response.body.$.book_id}}",
  "chapter_ids": ["2", "2.1", "2.2"]
}

### 8. Generate Marp presentation (run step 2 first)

POST {{apiUrl}}/epub/marp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": "{{extractEpub.response.body.$.book_id}}",
  "marp_output": "{{marpOutput}}",
  "title": "My Book Summary",
  "include_summaries": true,
  "include_content": false,
  "max_depth": 3
}

